eding the application.</p><p>E.g. You changed jobs 3 times in the 12 months preceding your application and you are working on the day of the application. Between your 1st and 2nd employment, you were not employed for 3 days. Between your 2nd and 3rd employment, you were not employed for 4 days. You may qualify because you were not connected by an employment contract for a maximum of 10 days.</p><p><strong>Teaching staff</strong> must demonstrate 12 months of employment (full-time or part-time), not necessarily in the same school. The major holiday period is assimilated to periods worked. But there cannot be more than 10 'unemployed' days in those 12 months.</p><p><strong>Ability to work</strong></p><p>At the time of application, you must be fully incapacitated for work and not in employment with the permission of the medical advisor of the health insurance fund.</p><p>You must <strong>not be unfit for work at the</strong> time of application or <strong>in the 12-month period before the application date</strong>. You are unfit for work if you receive disability benefits from the health insurance fund and have no other professional income.</p><p>There is an exception for breaks following statutory maternity leave and breastfeeding leave.</p><h3>Loan</h3><p>You must have taken out a mortgage loan for:</p><ul><li><strong>building</strong> a home</li><li><strong>buying</strong> a home</li><li>buying <strong>and renovating</strong> a home</li><li><strong>renovating</strong> a home (an additional loan for conversion or extension work is also possible).</li></ul><p>You must apply for the insurance <strong>within the year</strong> after the credit institution makes the money (or part of the money) available to you (first capital drawdown).</p><p>For <strong>new construction</strong>, the date on which the money is made available for building the home applies. Under certain conditions, the loan for the building plot can also be co-insured. Contact the Flemish Housing Fund for this.</p><p>The amount borrowed is:</p><ul><li>a minimum of 50,000 euros for building, buying or buying and renovating a home</li><li>at least 25,000 euros for renovating your home.</li></ul><p>The following loans <strong>are not </strong>eligible for insurance:</p><ul><li>a <strong>refinancing of an existing loan</strong>, when you did <strong>not</strong> already <strong>have insurance</strong> (if you already had insurance, it continues to run).</li><li>a loan to finance another loan</li><li>a loan to purchase only a building plot.</li></ul><h3>Home</h3><p>The home must:</p><ul><li>be your <strong>only home</strong>. You and the co-occupiers are not full owners of another home unless that home has been declared unfit.</li><li>Be your <strong>main residence</strong> or become your main residence. You must state the (probable) date on the application document.<br>Please note: you can only receive an allowance from the moment you live in the house.</li><li>Be located in the <strong>Flemish Region</strong>.</li></ul><p>The estimated sales value (without registration duties or VAT) of the home + building plot (including new construction) by the bank does not exceed:</p><ul><li>378,120 euros for houses in the Flemish <strong>Region</strong></li><li>434,830 euro for houses in listed <a href=\"https://www.vlaamswoningfonds.be/sites/default/files/inline-files/Overzicht%20gemeenten%20verhoogde%20verkoopwaarde.pdf\">municipalities with a higher average sales value</a>.</li></ul>","nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"<p><strong>Op het moment van de aanvraag</strong> moet je aan een aantal voorwaarden voldoen.</p><p>Om in aanmerking te komen voor de gratis verzekering mag je <strong>geen andere verzekering</strong> van de Vlaamse overheid tegen inkomensverlies hebben.</p><h3>Werk</h3><p>Je bent volledig arbeidsgeschikt en je oefent een beroepsactiviteit uit.</p><p><strong>Beroepsactiviteit</strong></p><p>Je bent al minstens <strong>12 opeenvolgende maanden aan het werk</strong>:</p